name: C Salt Gourmet Market
directions: From the parking lot, go up the stairs to the main entrance, or use the handicap-accessible ramp to the left. Diagonally to your left will be a U-shaped counter for ordering food as well as food display cases. If you go to the left of this counter, on your left will be a small alcove with two male/female-signed single-occupancy restrooms. I used the one on the left. I imagine the one on the right is the same.
comment: Door handle is a lever type with a button lock on the stem. Bathroom has a toilet and sink; everything is handicap-accessible. It was clean and nice. The market itself is nice and the food is good, but the layout might be somewhat challenging to someone in a wheelchair depending on the chair's size.

name: Reuvens building (1st floor) (Leiden University)
directions: There are 4 entrances to the building(s) around the courtyard, so make sure you enter Reuvensplaats 3 specifically. Once you're inside, go around the corner to the left, go up one floor on the stairs on your right hand, and make a u-turn at the top of the stairs. You'll see the all-gender bathroom on your right hand side.
comment:
Two seperate stalls behind the door with the bathroom sign, both have bins.

This is a University building. It's a bit more quiet than the other buildings, and I'm unsure whether there are actual lectures/workgroups there. If you want an excuse at the ready (especially without a student ID), you could say you're supposed to meet with a friend/sibling/kid/... there. Then again, I don't think people will generally ask for your reason to be there (unless you look really lost)

name: Reuvens building (Leiden University)
directions: There are about 4 entrances from the courtyard, so make sure you enter at Reuvensplaats 3 specifically. Once you've entered, there is an all-gender, wheelchair accessible bathroom on your left hand.
comment:
[unsure about the changing table situation - haven't had a chance to check] 
This is a University Building. I am unsure whether any lectures/workgroups are given here, but if there are, I think the groups may be a bit on the smaller side. I would not recommend saying you're here for a student-for-a-day day if you don't have a student ID. If someone you don't know approaches you, you could probably say you're supposed to meet a friend/sibling/kid/... there instead, but I don't think people will ask unless you look really lost.
